when I was a kid I couldn't tell the difference between dreams and reality and I kept having mundane dreams about myself getting good grades in an upcoming test or myself getting the cool toy at mcdonalds or one time I got a game boy advance. 

but most nights I'd wake up and it would be gone like it was stolen or something and I'd search the house. nothing.

I kept a drawer in my dresser(top right). with things that were "too good to be true". i'd put all the stuff that had the potential to disappear and I'd check it everyday before and after I went to sleep. 

sometimes stuff would be missing and I knew that entire day was a dream. It was very frustrating. 

one day I put my favourite gameboy game(PowerQuest) back in the drawerr and It turned out to be missing... I dreamt it up. I got that game a year ago for my birthday. that entire year was a fucking dream. holy shit. freakout. I couldnt breathe. sitting on my bed bawling my eyes out. went to sleep. sucked it up. 

 i tried to stay awake as long as possible because I didn't know who would wake up the next day. 

went to school like nothing happened, avoided friends.
councillor noticed and  i just kind of hung out with him everyday like a fucking idiot.

I stopped using the drawer, I didn't want to know anymore.

my entire life is a fucking waste of time. 

some few years later(maybe 3), the school takes us skiing. this was the first time I've ever been skiing so I'm pretty pumped. I never use my boots and never put them on in the entryway. havn't done that since I played in the snow as a (smaller)kid... I can't find my gloves and feel around for them between the shoeracks 
I feel a nintendo cartridge. 
I froze. 

everything comes back to me, I sit there in shock almost sniffing tears again. 
(i'm a baby, I cry a lot. I was a very emotional kid.) 
then I laughed. 
who the fuck

TURN OUT I JUST FUCKING DREAMT THAT I PUT IT IN THE DRAWER THAT NIGHT WHEN I REALLY JUST MISPLACED IT UNDER THE DAMN SHOERACK

I was so mad at myself hahaha

oh well, it's a thing.

One time when I broke my collar bone, I was admitted to the hospital... I might have been drinking that night... And I might have fallen over on my bicycle...
And I might not have any real memories from the previous night. But my friend had home made wine from his mother's cabinet so we drank it.    

When I fell, I felt my arm collapse under me. My arm lay flat to my chest. It was weird. 
I called my parents but they were both out of province like they usually were, so I called a taxi to pick me up and take me to the hospital. 
 
I went in and came back out, same driver was there waiting for me. 

The taxi driver was nice, but he was upset that they didn't give me any pain killers. So he gave me some in the car on the way back to my house urging me to take them there, I decided to put them in my pocket for when I really needed them.

I slept on the sofa that night. Woke up to pain around 10am,
Rummaged in my pocket for a pill and dry swallowed it. 

Shortly after I got up to pee. My vision went black like it usually did if I got up from laying down too quickly.
